-- Johannesburg Stock Exchange to Restore Services After Halting Share Trades
-- Antony Sguazzin
-- 2010-07-27T12:41:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/johannesburg-stock-exchange-to-restore-services-after-halting-share-trades.html

          
          
             JSE Ltd., which runs Africa’s
biggest stock exchange, says services are being restored after
trading was halted by a technical problem earlier today.  
 Johannesburg’s JSE commented in a mobile phone text alert
to clients today.  
          
          


  


        